    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a superlative 2004 BMW M3 (E46) Coupe, finished in Carbon Black Metallic. This specimen is powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L straight-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system that has been fully rebuilt with Beisan components. Power is delivered through a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox to a variable M-differential lock. The chassis is structurally sound with documented rear subframe reinforcement and fresh Powerflex bushings throughout. Preventative maintenance is exhaustive, including recent rod bearing replacement and a cooling system overhaul with a Stewart high-performance water pump. The exterior retains its factory depth and luster, while the interior Nappa leather remains supple with no bolster wear. This is a turn-key, investment-grade driver's car with zero deferred maintenance.",
